Use busybox to make the file system

Why? In linux, all is file, and user operate the system by file call. In addition, it is the interface of user and underlying starage.

Root file system composes of shell commands, libs, char sets and setting script and stands for /

What is busybox?  a set of linux commands and tools, a tool to make embeded file system.

Use it :
	1) download the resource code : https://www.busybox.net/downloads/
	   remove to home/ : cp -r xxx /home;    tar xvf xxx
	2) modify makefile : ARCH=arm      CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabi-
	3) configure : make defconfig      make menuconfig
	4) compile : make -j4   # using four processes to speed up the make rate
	5) install : make install

Error log : scripts/kconfig/lxdialog/dialog.h:31:20: fatal error: curses.h: No such file or directory   -------           sudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev libncursesw5-dev

Make file system by busybox in /home:
	1) mkdir rootfs
	2) mkdir rootfs/lib
	3) cp -r busybox-xxx/_install/* rootfs
	4) cp -p /usr/arm-linux-gnueabi/bin/* rootfs/lib
	5) mkdir -p rootfs/dev/  &  cd rootfs/dev
	6) mknod -m 666 tty1 c 4 1
	7) mknod -m 666 tty2 c 4 2
	8) mknod -m 666 tty3 c 4 3
	9) mknod -m 666 tty4 c 4 4
	10) mknod -m 666 console c 5 1
	11) mknod -m 666 null c 1 3

Make SD card file system mimior:
	1) dd if=/dev/zero of=rootfs.ext3 bs=1M count=32
	2) mkfs.ext3 rootfs.ext3
	3) mount -t ext3 rootfs.ext3 /mnt/ -o loop
	4) cp -r rootfs/* /mnt
	5) umount /mnt

Start Kernel and load rootfs:
	1) qemu-system-arm -M vexpress-a9 -m 512M -dtb./vexpress-v2p-ca9 -kernel./zImage -nographic -append "root=/dev/mmcblk0 rw console=ttyAMA0" -sd rootfs.ext3
	2) Start Kernel using graph: remove the option -nographic
